.TH "bch_next_delay" 9 "bch_next_delay" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bch_next_delay \- update ratelimiting statistics and calculate next delay
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "uint64_t" bch_next_delay
.BI "(struct bch_ratelimit *d "  ","
.BI "uint64_t done "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "d" 12
the struct bch_ratelimit to update
.IP "done" 12
the amount of work done, in arbitrary units
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Increment \fId\fP by the amount of work done, and return how long to delay in
jiffies until the next time to do some work.
